  "texts": [
    "Harmonizing data is rarely equivalent to building a universally complete or coherent dataset.",
    "That is, putting aside the issue of what may be lost in creating a harmonized dataset, the harmonized dataset itself often has limitations that should be acknowledged and evaluated.",
    "Here we consider limits in the volume of data that can be harmonized as well as the subsequent validity of harmonized data.",
    "One real limitation is that observations included in the harmonized datasets are often only a subset of what could theoretically be collected.",
    "That is, if the underlying datasets do not themselves contain the desired data, then the harmonized data will also face the same data limitations."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}